.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.log
.firebase/
js/.trash-*

# Local config files with your own values (API keys, deployed Cloud Function URLs) — never
# committed, so this repo can stay public without leaking anything you fill in later (Stripe
# keys included, once that config file exists). Each has a *.example.js counterpart that IS
# tracked, with blank placeholders — copy the example to the real filename and fill it in.
# firebase-config.js is the one deliberate exception: its values are safe to expose by design
# (see the comment in that file — access is enforced by Firestore Security Rules, not by hiding
# this config), so it's un-ignored below and stays committed with real values.
js/*-config.js
!js/firebase-config.js
